                <summary>All the businesses in the city of Staunton closed on Saturday as citizens
                    observed the governor's call for a day of mourning for the victims of the
                    Richmond disaster. "In our remembrance, we have never seen a day so markedly
                    kept, exhibiting thereby the exceeding sympathy of our people, white and
                    colored, for those who suffered the late disaster in Richmond. Contributions
                    have been liberally given."</summary>
